$ System.Data.DataTable (class)

A `System.Data.DataTable` object represents *one* in-memory table of → development/Data. It is the central object in the → Microsoft/dot-net/ADO environment.

A parent-child relationship between two *DataTable's* can be established with a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataRelation[`System.Data.DataRelation`].

→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataTableReader[`System.Data.DataTableReader`] obtains the contents of one or more `DataTable` objects in the form of one or more read-only, forward-only result sets and
thus allows to iterate over the rows in a `DataTable`.

sa:

  Compare with → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataSet[`System.Data.DataSet`]
